'''North Valley Hospital''' is a [[Nonprofit organization|nonprofit]] [[Internal medicine|general medicine]] and [[Surgery|surgical]] hospital located in [[Whitefish, Montana]].<ref>{{cite web
|url=http://health.usnews.com/best-hospitals/area/mt/north-valley-hospital-6810550/details
|title= North Valley Hospital
|author=
|publisher= U.S. News
|date= 
|accessdate=26 May 2014}}</ref> It is a state-designated community [[trauma center]]<ref>{{cite web
|url=http://www.dailyinterlake.com/news/local_montana/whitefish-hospital-gets-trauma-designation/article_8f9f7f81-7b2a-5429-b6d7-e9448a229d68.html
|title= Whitefish hospital gets trauma designation
|author=
|publisher= The Daily Inter Lake
|date= 21 May 2009
|accessdate=26 May 2014}}</ref> that serves Whitefish and the broader community of [[Flathead County, Montana|Flathead]] and [[Lincoln County, Montana|Lincoln]] County. The hospital's [[chief executive officer]] is Jason Spring and it is managed by Quorum Health Resources.<ref>{{cite web
|url=http://www.dailyinterlake.com/news/local_montana/north-valley-hospital-hires-new-ceo/article_e9a025c3-7280-5f75-b85d-c647c3955843.html
|title= North Valley Hospital hires new CEO
|author=
|publisher= The Daily Inter Lake
|date= 8 January 2009
|accessdate=26 May 2014}}</ref> It is a member of the [[Planetree Alliance]].<ref name=planetree>{{cite web
|url=http://www.whitefishpilot.com/whitefishpilot/nvh-celebrates-years-of-planetree/article_57fdee7e-e71a-5fa3-bb51-aec30aa5aff9.html
|title= NVH celebrates 10 years of Planetree
|author= Matt Baldwin
|publisher= Whitefish Pilot
|date= 29 August 2012
|accessdate=26 May 2014}}</ref>

==History==
North Valley Hospital's history traces back to Whitefish, Montana<U+2019>s first hospital, which opened in 1905.<ref name=dailyinterlake100>{{cite web
|url=http://nvhosp.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/DIL-History-April-2005.pdf
|title= Hospital spans a century
|author= Lynnette Hintze
|publisher= The Daily Inter Lake
|date= 10 April 2005
|accessdate=26 May 2014}}</ref> The hospital was owned by [[Great Northern Railway (U.S.)|Great Northern Railway]] and Dr. Hugh E. Houston, a Great Northern Railway physician, served as the hospital<U+2019>s first doctor.<ref>{{cite web
|url=http://nvhosp.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/NVH-Article-Flathead-Living-2005.pdf
|title= North Valley Hospital: The Center of Healing for a Century!
|author= Gina Barker
|publisher= Flathead Living
|date= November/December 2005
|accessdate=26 May 2014}}</ref> Its first patients were mostly people injured in railroad accidents.<ref name=dailyinterlake100/> Mr. Peter Gutensohn and Mrs. J.A. Sampson acquired Northern Valley from the railroad in 1912.<ref name=dailyinterlake100/> They operated the hospital until the hospital building was converted into an apartment building in 1923.<ref name=dailyinterlake100/> The town was without a hospital from 1923 until 1936.<ref name=bigmove>{{cite web
|url=http://www.whitefishpilot.com/news/hospital-counting-the-hours-to-big-move/article_f8e9a853-5db4-5fbf-98ee-ee1383995d85.html
|title= Hospital counting the hours to big move
|author= Constance See
|publisher= Whitefish Pilot
|date= 15 March 2007
|accessdate=26 May 2014}}</ref> The building was converted back into a hospital by Mrs. J.A. Earhart.<ref name=dailyinterlake100/>

Dr. Edith Boyd purchased the hospital in 1941 and operated it until 1947.<ref name=dailyinterlake100/> In 1946, the hospital moved locations and was named after Dr. John B. Simons.<ref name=bigmove/> The hospital was later named North Valley Hospital Auxiliary.<ref name=dailyinterlake100/> Dr. Simons sold his interest in the hospital to a civic board in 1961.<ref name=dailyinterlake100/> North Valley Hospital Auxiliary was renamed Whitefish Memorial Hospital.<ref name=dailyinterlake100/>

A third hospital was planned and broke ground in 1969.<ref name=dailyinterlake100/> That hospital, named North Valley Hospital, opened in July 1974.<ref name=bigmove/> It was expanded by 56 beds in a 1975 renovation, which cost $1.375 million.<ref name=bigmove/> The hospital was again expanded in 1988.<ref name=bigmove/> Quorum Health Resources became the hospital's manger in 1990.<ref name=dailyinterlake100/> North Valley Hospital became a member of the [[Planetree Alliance]] network of hospitals in 1992.<ref name=planetree/>

===Expansion===
In 2000, hospital administrators decided to relocate North Valley Hospital.<ref name=bigmove/> The hospital<U+2019>s new $30 million facility, located on the south end of Whitefish, opened in March 2007.<ref>{{cite web
|url=http://www.dailyinterlake.com/news/local_montana/meet-the-new-north-valley-hospital/article_502fcc45-896c-5d24-ad86-8dca8bf7bf84.html
|title= Meet the new North Valley Hospital
|author= Candace Chase
|publisher= The Daily Inter Lake
|date= 19 February 2007
|accessdate=26 May 2014}}</ref> North Valley Hospital built a new facility for North Country Medical Clinic in [[Eureka, Montana]] in 2008. That same year, the hospital began operating The Base Lodge Clinic at Whitefish Mountain Resort annually from December until April.<ref>{{cite web
|url=http://nvhosp.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/NVH_2009CommunityReport.pdf
|title= Community Report
|author=
|publisher= North Valley Hospital
|date= 2009
|accessdate=26 May 2014}}</ref>

The hospital purchased The Professional Center in [[Columbia Falls, Montana]] in August 2010. The center was renamed North Valley Professional Center. North Valley Hospital also opened the West Glacier Clinic in 2010.<ref name=report2011>{{cite web
|url=http://nvhosp.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/NVH_2011CommunityReport.pdf
|title= Community Report
|author=
|publisher= North Valley Hospital
|date= 2011
|accessdate=26 May 2014}}</ref> The clinic is open from June until mid-September.<ref name=report2011/> North Valley Hospital acquired Glacier Maternity later that year.<ref>{{cite web
|url=http://issuu.com/invisionmt/docs/mtwoman-august2011
|title= North Valley Hospital's Birthing Center
|author= Cindy Branch
|publisher= Montana Woman
|date= August 2011
|accessdate=26 May 2014}}</ref>

North Valley Embrace Health, a structured outpatient mental health clinic, was opened in 2011.<ref>{{cite news|
|title=Flathead Beacon 
|date=Aug 3, 2011}}</ref> In April 2013, the North Valley Hospital began a $1.7 million expansion, which added a fourth operating room to its main facility.<ref name=abcfox>{{cite web
|url=http://www.abcfoxmontana.com/story/23701009/hospital-keeps-growing-to-meet-need
|title= Hospital Keeps Growing to Meet Need
|author= Parker Collins
|publisher= abc Montana
|date= 15 October 2013
|accessdate=26 May 2014}}</ref> The new operating room included the infrastructure to operate the [[da Vinci Surgical System]].<ref name=abcfox/> The expansion was completed in October of that year.<ref>{{cite web
|url=http://www.dailyinterlake.com/news/local_montana/hospital-expands-surgery-facilities/article_72919304-36c1-11e3-bb59-0019bb2963f4.html
|title= Hospital expands surgery facilities
|author= Ryan Murray
|publisher= The Daily Inter Lake
|date= 16 October 2013
|accessdate=26 May 2014}}</ref>

North Valley Geriatric Specialty Services opened in January 2014.<ref>{{cite news|
|title=Full -service practice
|publisher=Daily Inter Lake
|date=February 5, 2014
|author=Ryan Murray}}</ref> The hospital also operates North Valley Physical Therapy, a [[physical therapy]] and rehabilitation clinic in [[Columbia Falls, Montana]].<ref name=community>{{cite web
|url=http://nvhosp.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/2014-Community-Report.pdf
|title= Community Report
|author=
|publisher= North Valley Hospital
|date= 2014
|accessdate=26 May 2014}}</ref>

==Operations==
North Valley Hospital has four core departments: [[emergency department]]; Center for [[Invasiveness_of_surgical_procedures#Minimally_invasive_procedure|Minimally Invasive Surgery]]; Center for [[Orthopedic surgery|Orthopedics]]; and The Birth Center.<ref name=community/> North Valley Hospital's [[emergency department]], laboratories and imaging facilities are open 24 hours a day, 7 days a week.<ref name=community/> The laboratory has been certified by [[College of American Pathologists]] certified since 1997.<ref name=community/> The hospital's Center for Minimally Invasive Surgery utilizes the [[da Vinci Surgical System]] and other technologies to make surgical operations as minimally invasive as possible.<ref>{{cite web
|url=http://nvhosp.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Technology-to-Heal-with-Minimally-Invasive-Surgery-Montana-Woman-Feb-2012.pdf
|title= Technology to Heal with Minimal Invasiveness
|author=
|publisher= Montana Journal
|date= February 2012
|accessdate=26 May 2014}}</ref><ref name=flathead>{{cite web
|url=http://nvhosp.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/FBJ-11-2010-Minimally-Invasive-Surgery.pdf
|title= Minimally invasive
|author= Shelley Ridenour
|publisher= Flathead Business Journal
|date= 15 November 2010
|accessdate=26 May 2014}}</ref> Doctors at North Valley Hospital began using the da Vinci Surgical System in 2010.<ref name=flathead/> The Center for Orthopedics also utilizes [[computer-assisted surgery]] and has orthopedic nurse coordinators to assist in patient care.<ref>{{cite web
|url=http://nvhosp.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Dr-Bailey-in-Flathead-Living-July-2012.pdf
|title= Hitting Your Stride
|author= Clint Walker
|publisher= Flathead Living
|date= Summer 2012
|accessdate=26 May 2014}}</ref> The Birth Center utilizes [[obstetrics|obstetricians]], certified [[nurse midwife|nurse midwives]] and [[family medicine|family practitioners]].<ref name=community/>

The hospital also offers [[alternative medicine]] practices such as [[acupuncture]], [[massage therapy]] and [[water birth|water birthing]].<ref>{{cite web
|url=http://www.dailyinterlake.com/news/local_montana/article_2b003d3e-a36f-11e0-8a0e-001cc4c002e0.html
|title= May births break records at Whitefish hospital
|author=
|publisher= The Daily Inter Lake
|date= 1 July 2011
|accessdate=26 May 2014}}</ref>

==Planetree membership==
North Valley Hospital is a member<ref name=planetree/> of the Planetree network of hospitals, which seeks to promote patient-centered care.<ref name=planetreeorg>{{cite web
|url=http://planetree.org/about-planetree/
|title= About Us
|author=
|publisher= Planetree
|date=
|accessdate=26 May 2014}}</ref> The network is organized around ten components.<ref name=planetreeorg/> Planetree-inspired initiatives at the hospital include a medical library for patients and community members, patient massages, "spiritual care" programs and [[animal-assisted therapy]].<ref name=planetree/>

